                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d9">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/32084; Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lane</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-11-29T15:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 29, 1943—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 8:56 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2162. Although members of the Government express cordial enthusiasm regarding
                    Colombia’s new international position and the liberal press emphasizes the
                    importance of the Government’s decision there is virtual public apathy regarding
                    latest developments. There are no flags flying nor are there any public
                    demonstrations. Having witnessed popular enthusiasm following anti-Nazi action
                    on part of the Yugoslav and Costa Rican Governments it is to me almost
                    unbelievable that life in Bogotá can continue without any interruption whatever
                    on the occasion of the Colombian Government having taken such a momentous
                    decision. The Consul at Cali reports “a surprising <pb facs="0021" n="7"
                        xml:id="pg_7"/> lack of interest on the part of the local populace regarding
                    Colombia’s belligerency.”</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lane</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
